    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "787d9ca9f5396afba17ad16cb793d76ec9039021066f99587841ec9d7a9f8939",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "Asked by Hofstadter. The sequence begins $1,1,2,3,3,4,\\ldots$ and is A005185 in the OEIS. It is not even known whether $f(n)$ is well-defined for all $n$."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "a4ead2bb9e2033d77e6ccbc16ab786c5cb3015e8958a615230c7bc9c74917ff4",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $f(1)=f(2)=1$ and for $n>2$\\[f(n) = f(n-f(n-1))+f(n-f(n-2)).\\]Does $f(n)$ miss infinitely many integers? What is its behaviour?"
    }
  },
